Ajay Banga has been approved by the World Bank's Board of Governors as the next President of the institution. The author congratulates Banga and believes that he will bring transformation, expertise, experience, and innovation to the position. They also expect him to address global challenges, particularly poverty reduction and climate change. Banga's role will involve bringing together the public and private sectors, as well as philanthropies, to make necessary changes in development finance. The author looks forward to working with Banga and supporting his efforts to transform the World Bank and reduce poverty worldwide.